title: Murray, Carroll lead Eagles to 27-7 win over Giants - Erie Times News
text:
Philadelphia Eagles tight end Zach Ertz is tackled by New York Giants middle linebacker Uani' Unga and free safety Landon Collins during the first half of an NFL football game Monday, Oct. 19, 2015, in Philadelphia. The Associated Press DeMarco Murray ran for 109 yards and a touchdown, Nolan Carroll returned one of Manning's two interceptions for a score and the Philadelphia Eagles beat the New York Giants 27-7 Monday night.
 Erie Times News.
